comment.text: This translation key is used to display the file ID as a label or placeholder. It appears on various screens in the UI, such as a settings page, where users can edit the file ID and preview changes before applying them.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Azerbaijani translation 'Fay ID' is a misspelling and does not accurately convey 'File ID'. The correct translation would incorporate the Azerbaijani word for 'file'.

The Lao translation "D ໄຟລ໌" is not an accurate translation of "File ID". "D" typically means 'of' or 'belonging to', which isn't appropriate in this context. A more accurate translation would involve combining "file" with an identifier term.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ໄອດີໄຟລ໌ (Ai Di File) or ລະຫັດໄຟລ໌ (Ra-hat File)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao script uses a space after the classifier 'D' when it precedes a noun. While not strictly incorrect, the space might improve readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: D ໄຟລ໌ -> D ໄຟລ໌

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'ID fișier' is a literal translation and might not be the most natural or idiomatic way to express 'File ID' in Romanian. While technically correct, it's a bit clunky.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider 'Identificator fișier' or 'Număr identificare fișier'. Alternatively, keeping 'ID fișier' is acceptable if brevity is paramount.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'ගොනුවේ හැඳු.' while understandable, is not the most natural or accurate translation of "File ID". It literally translates to "File's Identity".  A more common and accurate translation would be "ගොනුවෙ ඩීඅයිඩී" (Gonuwe D.I.D.) or "ගොනුවෙ හැඳුම් පත" (Gonuwe hadanum pata).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using "ගොනුවෙ ඩීඅයිඩී" (Gonuwe D.I.D.) or "ගොනුවෙ හැඳුම් පත" (Gonuwe hadanum pata).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian (Cyrillic) translation 'ID датотеке' is not the most natural or accurate translation of 'File ID'. It literally translates to 'ID of file'. A more idiomatic and accurate translation would be 'ИД датотеке' or 'Број датотеке'.
